      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for the declared model risk.",
      "rationale": "All three FEA solvers (FDA in-house, Ansys 2022 R2, DePuy Synthes internal) operate under documented software quality management systems with version control, regression testing, and release validation records. Achieved level 3 exceeds the required level 2 for this model risk category."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Benchmark verification problems from NAFEMS and ASME V&V 10 were executed for each solver. Contact mechanics and large-displacement beam-column benchmarks confirmed correct implementation. Achieved level 3 exceeds required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence studies were performed on the pedicle screw, rod, and vertebral body surrogate components. Richardson extrapolation confirmed discretization error below 2% for peak von Mises stress and construct stiffness quantities of interest. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver residual tolerances were set to 1e-6 for force and displacement norms. Nonlinear convergence was confirmed for all load steps across all 11 construct configurations. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Simulation execution was performed by trained analysts following documented simulation plans. Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and post-processing scripts was conducted by a second qualified engineer at each institution. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic material models with titanium alloy properties (Ti-6Al-4V, E=114 GPa, nu=0.34) were applied to all metallic components. Contact interactions at screw-rod interfaces used penalty formulation with friction coefficient mu=0.23 from tribology literature. Model form is well-established for metallic spinal implant stiffness prediction. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Material properties sourced from certified material test reports for the production lot used in both experimental and simulation work. Geometric inputs derived from CMM measurements of test articles (dimensional tolerance ±0.01 mm). Torque values for screw-rod locking captured with calibrated torque wrench (±2% accuracy). Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (FDA CDRH and an ISO 17025-accredited external facility). Sample sizes consistent with ASTM F1717 guidance. Traceability of each test article to lot certification maintained. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Testing was performed under a single loading condition (static compression-bending at 5 degrees, per ASTM F1717). Dynamic and fatigue loading conditions were not included in this validation activity. This single test condition limits the achieved level to 2, which is below the required level of 3. This shortfall is documented and accepted given the intended static pre-market submission scope."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Simulation input parameters were matched to experimentally measured values for each of the 11 constructs individually, including measured screw spacing, rod length, and locking torque. Boundary conditions in FEA replicated fixture geometry as measured by CMM. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison performed using construct stiffness (N/mm) and yield load (N) as primary quantities of interest. Agreement assessed via ASME V&V 10.1 area validation metric and Bayesian model updating. Mean prediction error for stiffness: 3.8% (95% CI: 1.2–6.4%). Ensemble spread captured by prediction intervals overlapping 10/11 experimental observations. Achieved level 4 exceeds required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and yield load are the primary regulatory quantities required by FDA guidance for Class II spinal fixation pre-market submissions and are directly specified in ASTM F1717. These quantities are directly relevant to the clinical performance of the device in posterior lumbar fixation. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities directly replicate the ASTM F1717 test configuration specified in the submission requirement. The same device geometry, material lot, and loading protocol used in the validation are those referenced in the 510(k) submission. The validation boundary conditions are judged highly representative of the intended regulatory use. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/nagaraja-cou1-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/nagaraja-credibility-assessment-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for Model Risk Level 3 at Medium assurance. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because the submission scope is limited to static loading per ASTM F1717 and the regulatory decision does not require dynamic validation at this stage. The ensemble model approach across three independent solver implementations provides additional confidence in prediction fidelity. Overall credibility is judged sufficient to support the Class II 510(k) pre-market submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
